==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philistinism
<hw>Phi*lis"tin*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The condition,
character, aims, and habits of the class called Philistines. See
<er>Philistine</er>, 3.</def> <mark>[Recent]</mark>
<rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On the side of beauty and taste, vulgarity; on the side of morals
and feeling, coarseness; on the side of mind and spirit, unintelligence,
-- this is <qex>Philistinism</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phillipsite</ent>⟦br⟧
